FBIS4-16999 "drsov077_b_94028" FBIS-SOV-94-077 Daily Report 21 Apr 1994 RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS Military & Nuclear Issues Strategic Missiles Kept `in Case of an Attack' Strategic Missiles Kept `in Case of an Attack' LD2104124994 Moscow Radio Moscow World Service in English 1100 GMT 21 Apr 94 LD2104124994 Moscow Radio Moscow World Service English BFN [Text] The commander of the Strategic Forces Division, General Igor Sergeyev, says that Russia is loyal to its international obligations under the SALT II treaty [as heard]. A group of journalists was allowed to visit the division, that is deployed in the Volga region. They visited the headquarters and got acquainted with combat equipment of the division. General Sergeyev reported that the SS-20 medium range missiles had been liquidated in keeping with the treaty. As for the strategic missiles, they are targeted nowhere. They will be assigned a special task, the commander said, only in case of an attack on Russia.
